= System.getProperty(ALLOW_SELF_ATTACH_PROPERTY);\n        String originalLatentResolve = System.getProperty(ByteBuddyAgent.LATENT_RESOLVE);\n        Path marker = Files.createTempFile(\"blockhound-byte-buddy-agent\", \".marker\");\n        Files.deleteIfExists(marker);\n        Path virtualMachineJar = writeVirtualMachineJar();\n        Path agentJar = Files.createTempFile(\"blockhound-byte-buddy-agent\", \".jar\");\n        try {\n            System.setProperty(ALLOW_SELF_ATTACH_PROPERTY, Boolean.FALSE.toString());\n            System.setProperty(ByteBuddyAgent.LATENT_RESOLVE, Boolean.TRUE.toString());\n\n            assertThatThrownBy(ByteBuddyAgent::getInstrumentation)\n                    .isInstanceOf(IllegalStateException.class)\n                    .hasMessageContaining(\"Byte Buddy agent\");\n\n            ByteBuddyAgent.attach(agentJar.toFile(),\n                    () -> Long.toString(ProcessHandle.current().pid()),\n                    marker.toString(),\n                    new ExternalAttachmentProvider(virtualMachineJar.toFile()));\n\n            assertThat(marker).exists();\n            assertThat(Files.readString(marker)).contains(agentJar.toString());\n        } finally {\n            restoreProperty(ALLOW_SELF_ATTACH_PROPERTY, originalAllowSelfAttach);\n            restoreProperty(ByteBuddyAgent.LATENT_RESOLVE, originalLatentResolve);\n            Files.deleteIfExists(agentJar);\n            Files.deleteIfExists(marker);\n            Files.deleteIfExists(virtualMachineJar);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Path writeVirtualMachineJar() throws IOException {\n        Path jar = Files.createTempFile(\"blockhound-byte-buddy-virtual-machine\", \".jar\");\n        String resourceName = RecordingVirtualMachine.class.getName().replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n        try (InputStream inputStream = ByteBuddyAgentTest.class.getClassLoader().getResourceAsStream(resourceName)) {\n            assertThat(inputStream).isNotNull();\n            try (JarOutputStream jarOutputStream = new JarOutputStream(Files.newOutputStream(jar))) {\n                jarOutputStream.putNextEntry(new JarEntry(resourceName));\n                copy(inputStream, jarOutputStream);\n                jarOutputStream.closeEntry();\n            }\n        }\n        return jar;\n    }\n\n    private static void copy(InputStream inputStream, OutputStream outputStream) throws IOException {\n        byte[] buffer = new byte[8192];\n        int length;\n        while ((length = inputStream.read(buffer)) != -1) {\n            outputStream.write(buffer, 0, length);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreProperty(String name, String originalValue) {\n        if (originalValue == null) {\n            System.clearProperty(name);\n        } else {\n            System.setProperty(name, originalValue);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ExternalAttachmentProvider implements AttachmentProvider {\n        private final File virtualMachineJar;\n\n        private ExternalAttachmentProvider(File virtualMachineJar) {\n            this.virtualMachineJar = virtualMachineJar;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Accessor attempt() {\n            return new ExternalAttachmentAccessor(virtualMachineJar);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ExternalAttachmentAccessor implements Accessor {\n        private final File virtualMachineJar;\n\n        private ExternalAttachmentAccessor(File virtualMachineJar) {\n            this.virtualMachineJar = virtualMachineJar;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean isAvailable() {\n            return true;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean isExternalAttachmentRequired() {\n            return true;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Class<?> getVirtualMachineType() {\n            return RecordingVirtualMachine.class;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public ExternalAttachment getExternalAttachment() {\n            return new ExternalAttachment(RecordingVirtualMachine.class.getName(), Collections.singletonList(virtualMachineJar));\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class RecordingVirtualMachine {\n        private final String processId;\n\n        private RecordingVirtualMachine(String processId) {\n            this.processId = processId;\n        }\n\n        public static RecordingVirtualMachine attach(String processId) {\n            return new RecordingVirtualMachine(processId);\n        }\n\n        public void loadAgent(String agent, String argument) throws IOException {\n            Files.writeString(Path.of(argument), processId + System.lineSeparator() + agent);\n        }\n\n        public void loadAgentPath(String agent, String argument) throws IOException {\n            Files.writeString(Path.of(argument), processId + System.lineSeparator() + agent);\n        }\n\n        public void detach() {\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Troubleshooting class initialization**\n\nI'm noticing that import isn't initializing properly. In the test method, I should first set the property and then call ByteBuddyAgent, which seems fine. But I'm wondering, what if the class was initialized earlier? Should I only be testing the active class? It feels like that's not really the case since other tests only import Attacher, not ByteBuddyAgent. But I'm still clear that my class import doesn't initialize as expected.\n\n**Troubleshooting attachment issues**\n\nI'm running into an exception when trying to attach, which could be because the class file for the Byte Buddy installation is missing or unsupported. That’s not great! I could make the test expect an attachment failure. I also need to consider whether to get the instrumentation status after trying to attach. The doGet lines might be covered earlier by ByteBuddyAgent.getInstrumentation, but the attach function itself doesn't seem to call doGet. It's definitely a tricky situation!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_053aa169fd2341d7016a2929c64e248196b7cbda6ffb037d9f\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKSoIwJf9W8Uq1cBJZpfCOGaLu-6oPhkIsNUJaORf7i4RIuTZOGm_2MqHQE3f14QKl5P_psIIdLFC8YlXYma6jl7kxDZUCkeqoPPNcke2iqEXySeLdlAsp_sOoEZTYTAfzO9RTgdl5QsSR-9irsLdOgbiDNX0AY2uKyODmPLb3pM0NgggZtOgjjtHG1npVrx_mG_RA3s8qejp_ef6uP9f6F2lyNDgvyhzYIXRckpuUVkE91OUTKkpifhusoDw5P2FJf0vszua42EMXscQIEVIv_01uWOXGkElagu4V4RXNtWPP3D8m9eBQ_Ymik4yIYOtiENq2yx59C18GjRxaBreHv7zsoCoraTjGYvU-uTHA8BJt62j3lyAHZei3aSfGLDyNsqw1Uw04zqYDnX0l985obrWm1ecgwLn6X8cCSwPS8ur3DgSy9v7jDfFR2q7XLczzetvlE11NVZRsnbvsMLFXmc0DvShK6sd6WC7QTcEx0xNna4zbLvta4hCvfK_WD06OA76hwi2LSrkJgeK6hJb5AOR0KF3-l3v7s3pg0GD9n_Igm1Nhhb5YHhIbk-Frm5Fl1bX9UeYWzJNG-ABc5Vl2kdcXXl9PspybhpgfUoKDNR0SZi90MEmCJYMxFKWQNrV3HtG7u5B1u9hsm-D43h95XQGtqJtJB4EOaLjTiE6X9n8SFRQwC3JB7dBCB581r_x11t7AV5AxbUywGmQMKQvO